{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"Tighten the verifier IMPACT prompt for consistency (robustness, not a blocker). The severity\nattributes get zero anchoring in `plan_review_verifier.md` (vs the rich validity guidance), so\nadd per-attribute definitions, level anchors, and plan-aware framing to curb per-ticket\ninflation. Guarded by the `discriminates_impact_levels` eval already landed + the distribution\nreport. (Body/title were previously swapped with task ec89 — this restores the impact-prompt\nscope to its matching title and removes the accidental duplication of the docs+tests task 4cb9.)\n\nThis task is independent of the novelty/rising-floor chain (no hard dep); it hardens the impact\naxis the Pass-3 floor relies on so the verifier cannot regress to rating every finding the same\n(the severity-saturation the floor would be blind to).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Each severity attribute (prod_impact, debt_impact, blast_radius, likelihood, reversibility) has a definition + level anchors in `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_verifier.md` (+ `_agentic`)\n- [ ] Plan-stage framing for reversibility/blast_radius (a plan is pre-merge — anchor severity to the planned change, not a shipped system)\n- [ ] `discriminates_impact_levels` eval still passes (≥ its existing bar on the high/low pairs); `scripts/plan_review_impact_distribution.py` shows no regression to saturation","title":"Tighten the verifier impact prompt (robustness)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782766154161493001,"uuid":"e63888b2-9ce4-4c71-b96d-e5c5972096cf"}